# Allowed author/committer email patterns (POSIX ERE).
# Used by: `mise run identity:check`, CI policy workflow, and GitHub Protect main
# ruleset regexes (keep those in sync manually when this file changes).
# One pattern per line. Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
# A commit passes if BOTH author and committer emails match at least one pattern.

# Victor Software House org mail (human commits)
@victor-software-house\.com$

# GitHub web merges / UI commits (committer is often this exact address)
^noreply@github\.com$

# GitHub-generated user/bot noreply forms
# e.g. 123456+login@users.noreply.github.com
# e.g. 304785771+grokkybara[bot]@users.noreply.github.com
@users\.noreply\.github\.com$
